Exploratory analysis of COVID-19 data¶

COVID Admissions: Patients admitted as suspected or confirmed with COVID-19 Non Covid Admissions: Patients admitted without suspected or confirmed COVID-19 confirmed COVID hospitalisations: Patients who have received a positive COVID-19 test in the past 14 days Suspected COVID hospitalisations: Patients suspected to have COVID-19 who have not received a positive test in the past 14 days Non COVID hospitalisations: Patients without confirmed or suspected COVID-19 A&E Attendances: number of attendances in accident and emergency departments

Key Dates¶

From: https://research.senedd.wales/research-articles/coronavirus-timeline-welsh-and-uk-governments-response/

AE_attendances = pd.read_csv('A&E attendances.csv', names = ['Date','A&E attendances']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date') 
confirmed_hospitalisations = pd.read_csv('confirmed COVID hospitalisations.csv', names = ['Date','Confirmed COVID Hospitalisations']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date')  
suspected_hospitalisations = pd.read_csv('suspected COVID hospitalistaions.csv', names = ['Date','Suspected COVID Hospitalisations']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date') 
non_covid_hospitalisations = pd.read_csv('Non COVID hospitalisations.csv', names = ['Date','Non COVID Hospitalisations']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date')  
covid_admissions = pd.read_csv('COVID admissions (suspected and confirmed).csv', names = ['Date','COVID Admissions']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date') 
non_covid_admissions = pd.read_csv('Non COVID admissions.csv', names = ['Date','Non COVID Admissions']).drop(0, axis = 0).set_index('Date')

x = 7 #Defines length in days used for moving average

for n in range(x-1,491): #Calculates and stores x day moving average for dates covered by A&E attendances data
    df_RA['A&E attendances'].loc[n] = df_reset['A&E attendances'].loc[n-(x-1):n].agg(sum)/x
for n in range(0,x-1):
    df_RA['A&E attendances'].loc[n] = np.nan
for n in range(491,525):
    df_RA['A&E attendances'].loc[n] = np.nan #Stores all values where x day moving average is invalid as null

In [104]:
import datetime
In [105]:
def date_to_serial(year,month,day): #Converts date to format used by matplotlib
    ts = datetime.datetime(year,month,day).timestamp() #Gets timestamp of date
    serial = ts/86400 #Converts timestamp from seconds to days
    return serial
